    <summary>Utility to connect to Bambu Lab 3D printers: sign in, discover printers (cloud or LAN), send Bambu G-code/3MF files, and perform basic control actions.</summary>
    <description>Bambu Connect is a utility for integrating with Bambu Lab 3D printers via cloud or LAN.

### Features
- Sign in with a Bambu Lab cloud account
- View printers linked to the account; discover and connect to LAN-mode printers
- Import and send Bambu G-code or 3MF files to the printer
- Basic printer control (e.g., axis movement); live view may not be available in current builds

### What this package does
- Installs Bambu Connect for Windows via the official installer
- Suitable for unattended/automated deployments with Chocolatey

### Compatibility and requirements
- Windows 10/11 (per upstream support)
- Administrator privileges may be required

### Verification after installation
- Launch “Bambu Connect” and sign in or connect via LAN mode
- Send a small test file to verify connectivity

